---
import Layout from "@/components/Layout.astro"
import { en } from "@/content/home-en"
import "@/styles/home/index.css"

const meta = {
  ...en.meta,
  title: "Privacy · Kevin Gámez",
  ogTitle: "Privacy · Kevin Gámez",
  twitterTitle: "Privacy · Kevin Gámez",
  description: "What kevingamez.com collects, why, and how to opt out. First-party analytics, heatmaps, error logs.",
  ogDescription: "What kevingamez.com collects, why, and how to opt out. First-party analytics, heatmaps, error logs.",
  twitterDescription:
    "What kevingamez.com collects, why, and how to opt out. First-party analytics, heatmaps, error logs.",
  canonical: "https://kevingamez.com/privacy/",
  ogUrl: "https://kevingamez.com/privacy/",
  includeJsonLd: false,
  // Standalone, English-only page: don't advertise a Spanish alternate (there
  // isn't one) or point hreflang at the homepage.
  hreflang: [],
}
---

<Layout meta={meta}>
  <main class="privacy-page">
    <article class="wrap privacy-article">
      <header>
        <p class="kicker">Privacy</p>
        <h1>What this site collects</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          Plain-language list of every piece of data <a href="/">kevingamez.com</a> sees, why, and how to opt out. Last updated
          2026-05.
        </p>
      </header>

      <h2>The short version</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>No accounts, no logins, no marketing emails.</li>
        <li>Aggregate analytics — page views, sections viewed, device, country — never tied to you.</li>
        <li>
          Heatmaps and session replays via Microsoft Clarity (cursor moves, clicks, scroll). Form fields are masked by
          default.
        </li>
        <li>
          The <code>/api/chat</code> Claude console keeps your IP only for daily rate limiting (20 messages / IP / day) and
          forgets it within 24 hours.
        </li>
        <li>Nothing is sold or shared with third parties beyond the analytics vendors below.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Vendors and what they receive</h2>

      <h3>Google Analytics 4 (gtag)</h3>
      <p>
        Anonymous page-view counts and event names (e.g. <code>section_view</code>, <code>cta_click</code>), coarse
        country/device, referrer. IPs are anonymized at edge by Google before they hit the analytics dashboard.
      </p>

      <h3>Vercel Analytics + Speed Insights</h3>
      <p>
        First-party, cookieless. Records page paths, Core Web Vitals (LCP, INP, CLS) and country at country level. No
        persistent identifier.
      </p>

      <h3>Microsoft Clarity</h3>
      <p>
        Heatmaps and session replays. Records cursor movement, clicks, and scrolling on kevingamez.com. <strong
          >All input fields, including the live console, are masked</strong
        > — I see <em>that</em> you typed, not <em>what</em>. Clarity sets a session cookie scoped to this domain.
      </p>

      <h3>Anthropic (Claude · /api/chat)</h3>
      <p>
        When you use the live console, your message and the conversation history of that session are sent to Anthropic's
        API to generate a reply. Your IP is hashed in memory at the Vercel edge for rate-limiting and discarded at the
        end of each day. Conversations are not stored on the server.
      </p>

      <h2>How to opt out</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Block analytics.</strong> Most browser tracker-blockers (uBlock Origin, Brave Shields, Privacy Badger, Safari
          ITP) already block Google Analytics, Vercel and Clarity by default. The site still works fully.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Honor Do-Not-Track / Global Privacy Control.</strong> If your browser sends DNT or GPC, plan is to skip
          Clarity loading. (Coming next; until then, use a blocker.)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Don't use the console.</strong> If you don't type anything in <code>/#console</code>, nothing reaches
          Anthropic. Browsing the rest of the site doesn't trigger any LLM call.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Ask for deletion.</strong> Email <a href="mailto:kevingamez.kg@gmail.com">kevingamez.kg@gmail.com</a>
          and I'll wipe what I can (heatmap recordings tied to a session ID, GA event log).
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><code>_ga</code>, <code>_ga_*</code> — Google Analytics, ~1 year.</li>
        <li><code>_clck</code>, <code>_clsk</code> — Microsoft Clarity, session + 1 year.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>That's it. No third-party advertising cookies, no remarketing pixels.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions or a deletion request: <a href="mailto:kevingamez.kg@gmail.com">kevingamez.kg@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>

      <p class="back"><a href="/">← Back to home</a></p>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .privacy-page {
    background: var(--cream);
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding: 80px 0 120px;
  }
  .privacy-article {
    max-width: 720px;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .privacy-article header {
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }
  .privacy-article .kicker {
    font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--coral-strong);
    margin: 0 0 12px;
  }
  .privacy-article h1 {
    font-family: "Instrument Serif", serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(40px, 6vw, 64px);
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 18px;
  }
  .privacy-article .lede {
    font-size: 17px;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    max-width: 56ch;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .privacy-article h2 {
    font-family: "Instrument Serif", serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 28px;
    line-height: 1.1;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 40px 0 12px;
  }
  .privacy-article h3 {
    font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--coral-strong);
    margin: 24px 0 8px;
  }
  .privacy-article p,
  .privacy-article ul {
    margin: 0 0 14px;
  }
  .privacy-article ul {
    padding-left: 20px;
  }
  .privacy-article li {
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .privacy-article a {
    color: var(--coral-strong);
    border-bottom: 1px dashed currentColor;
  }
  .privacy-article code {
    font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 13px;
    background: var(--cream-2);
    padding: 1px 6px;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }
  .privacy-article .back {
    margin-top: 48px;
    font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 13px;
  }
</style>
